					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The coordinate in OAM refers to the pixel location immediately above the pixel in the upper left corner of the sprite. For example, an 8x8 pixel sprite at x=16 y=111 will cover (16, 112) through (23, 119).
<br />
<br />
<br />EDIT: dang it, ninja'd again. Well at least it's better than pirated.</div>

