				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For collisions (X and Y are the values written to OAM):
<br />
<br />The left edge is at X;
<br />The right edge is at X + 8;
<br />The top edge is at Y - 1;
<br />The bottom edge is at Y + 7;
<br />
<br />You probably shouldn't be testing for collisions on the sprite level though, unless all your objects are 8x8 pixels. Since most objects have more than 1 sprite, it makes more sense to have coordinates for the objects, as well as their dimensions, and use that for collisions. The coordinates can also be used for rendering the sprites.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

